* administer the Environmental Registry established under section 6;
* prepare State of the Environment Reports under section 7;

In carrying out the functions outlined in subsection (1), the Director must do the following:
* prepare National Policies and National Plans under section 8;
* administer the Environmental Impact Assessment procedure under Part 3;
* prepare guidelines, standards, codes of practice and procedures;
* prepare advice on international environmental treaties and instruments, including implementation strategies;
* undertake environmental research, assessment, monitoring, and inspection generally;
* undertake such other duties and responsibilities as may lawfully be required by the Minister.
* the appointment of persons not employed by the Department as authorised officers for the purpose of administering this Act; and
* the establishment of committees for the purpose of ensuring better inter-departmental and inter-agency co-ordination on particular environmental matters.
* The Director may delegate to officers of the Department and any authorised officers appointed under paragraph (1)(a), such powers and functions as he or she considers appropriate, with the exception of this power of delegation.

A National State of the Environment Report must include all of the following:
* an assessment of the quality of Vanuatuâ¢s environment;
* an assessment of social and economic development trends and their likely impact upon the environment;
* a summary of government and private sector policies, programs and initiatives to address and monitor environmental management and conservation issues;
* such other matters as the Minister considers appropriate.
* to promote the environmentally sound and safe management and conservation of the natural resources of Vanuatu; and
* to provide for the co-ordination of related activities.
* to provide for the implementation of the National Policy; and
* to provide for the conservation and/or sustainable management and development of particular natural resources of Vanuatu.
* an evaluation of the current state of the particular matter that is the subject of the Policy;
* an evaluation of the social, human health, custom, economic and ecological considerations and issues in respect of that matter;
* a description of any relevant national priorities;
* an outline of the objectives to be achieved by the Policy;

All projects, proposals or development activities that:
* cause impacts relating to the matters listed in subsection (2);
* affect coastal dynamics or result in coastal erosion;
* result in the pollution of water resources;
* affect any protected, rare, threatened or endangered species, its habitat or nesting grounds;
* result in the contamination of land;
* endanger public health;
* affect important custom resources;
* affect protected or proposed protected areas;
* affect air quality;
* result in the unsustainable use of renewable resources;
* result in the introduction of foreign organisms and species;
* result in any other activity prescribed by regulation.

The Minister must do one of the following:
* approve the application with or without terms and conditions;
* refer the matter back to the Director for further assessment;
* reject the application.

The application must be in such form as is approved by the Director and include the following:
* the name and particulars of the applicant, including that of any associate, affiliate or party that may benefit or share in the research or obtain any benefit from such research;
* a full and accurate description of the nature and extent of the research that is to be undertaken, and the area where such research will take place;
* a description of the nature of any biological resource or traditional knowledge that is to be investigated;
* a statement concerning the nature of the research to be undertaken, including an outline of the investigation and sampling methods to be used;
* an outline of the nature, duration and extent of any expected commercial research and development plan that may result from the biodiversity prospecting;

